Wait, let me check the `after` signature. `after` takes a callback function. The promise chain should be inside it. Let me check:

```ts
after(() => {
  syncCatalog()
    .then(result => {
      console.log(`[sync] #${result.syncNumber} complete — invalidating "products" cache tag`);
      revalidateTag('products');
    })
    .catch(err => {
      console.error('[sync] background sync failed', err);
